## Live state — read these, keep these current

- `.claude/tasks/TASKS.md` — canonical task list, six statuses (`pending/running/needs-fix/broken/upgrading/completed`). Completed items move to `ARCHIVE.md` with a verification line.
- `.claude/state/status.json` — hook-maintained build/lint/tests health. Never hand-edit its `health` block.
- `.claude/GUIDE.md` — **the management system**: where every kind of file goes, who may write what, naming and lifecycle rules. Read it before creating any new file outside the source tree.

## How this harness is organized

- **Hooks** (`.claude/hooks/`) = deterministic enforcement, can hard-block. If a hook enforces something, there is no separate rule saying the same thing.
- **Rules** (`.claude/rules/`) = advisory conventions, read on demand: `safety.md`, `ship-verification.md`, `git-workflow.md`.
- **Skills** (`.claude/skills/`) = on-demand procedures: `/ship`, `/catchup`, `/learn`, `/harness-audit`.
- **Agents** (`.claude/agents/`) = isolated-context workers: `Explore` (haiku-pinned search), `small-executor` (one narrow step, persistent memory, completion gate), `small-verifier` (single-aspect checklist). Agents can't see this file — their prompts restate the house rules; don't replace those restatements with references.
- **Workflows** (`.claude/workflows/elevate.js`) = the small-model cascade: executor attempt → 3-aspect verifier panel → one evidence-injected retry → escalate to the session model.

## Self-healing & continuous learning

1. Every tool failure is recorded automatically (`capture-failure.sh` → `.claude/state/failure-ledger.jsonl`); signatures repeating ≥2× surface at session start.
2. `/learn` converts repeated failures and user corrections into per-file lessons (`.claude/memory/lessons/`, top-3 injected each session). Lessons need verbatim evidence; updates are deltas, never wholesale rewrites.
3. At weight ≥3.0, mechanically checkable lessons are promoted into hooks or `.claude/evals/regressions/` checks; judgment-only lessons get one line here.
4. `/harness-audit` is the self-maintenance pass; bare `/loop` routes through finish-work → `/learn` → audit → next task (see `.claude/loop.md`).

Evidence base for all of the above: `.claude/memory/research/` — read the relevant digest before removing or "simplifying" a mechanism.

